461
00:42:02,340 --> 00:42:05,060
We would fight for the rights of the civilians.

462
00:42:06,270 --> 00:42:08,080
I remember.

463
00:42:12,040 --> 00:42:13,870
When I was a child,

464
00:42:15,180 --> 00:42:17,130
suddenly, one day,

465
00:42:18,240 --> 00:42:22,040
my smoking-addicted father was lying on the bed,

466
00:42:22,040 --> 00:42:24,650
he never opened his eyes again.

467
00:42:24,650 --> 00:42:27,510
He exhausted the last cent of the family.

468
00:42:28,410 --> 00:42:32,300
Since then, my mother and I...

469
00:42:33,260 --> 00:42:37,110
had been living a life for everyone to step on us.

